<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm221544288">
<term>normal capacity</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm224085760">company’s maximum production level, without adding additional production resources, or within the company’s relevant range</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm207751760">
<term>relevant range</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm217739616">quantitative range of units that can be produced based on the company’s current productive assets; for example, if a company has sufficient fixed assets to produce up to 10,000 units of product, the relevant range would be between 0 and 10,000 units</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm199490224">
<term>special order</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm201140224">one-time order that does not typically affect current sales</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
</document>